<p>Build complex units from simpler ones using arithmetic operators. This allows you to express
any derived unit naturally.</p>

<h3>Unit Multiplication and Division</h3>

<pre><code class="language-lean">open Measures.Units.SI

-- Create velocity unit from meter and second
def velocity := meter / second
def speed := 25.0 *: velocity  -- 25 m/s

-- Create derived units
def energyUnit := newton * meter  -- N·m = J
def work := 100.0 *: energyUnit

-- Force unit from base units
def forceUnit := kilogram * meter / (second * second)  -- kg·m/s² = N</code></pre>

<h3>Unit Powers</h3>

<pre><code class="language-lean">-- Square and cube
def area := meter.sq       -- m²
def volume := meter.cube   -- m³

-- Area calculation
def roomArea := 25.0 *: meter.sq

-- Volume calculation
def tankVolume := 1000.0 *: meter.cube  -- 1000 m³</code></pre>

<h3>Reciprocal Units</h3>

<pre><code class="language-lean">-- Frequency is reciprocal of time
def freq := second.recip  -- 1/s = Hz
def frequency := 60.0 *: freq  -- 60 Hz

-- Wave number
def waveNumber := meter.recip  -- 1/m</code></pre>

<h3>General Powers</h3>

<pre><code class="language-lean">-- Arbitrary integer powers
def m4 := meter.pow 4   -- m⁴ (moment of inertia per density)
def invSq := meter.pow (-2)  -- m⁻²

-- Higher-order units
def specificEnergy := joule / kilogram  -- J/kg = m²/s²</code></pre>

<h3>Complex Expressions</h3>

<pre><code class="language-lean">-- Gravitational constant unit: m³/(kg·s²)
def gravUnit := meter.cube / (kilogram * second.sq)

-- Pressure: N/m² = kg/(m·s²)
def pressureUnit := newton / meter.sq

-- Viscosity: Pa·s = kg/(m·s)
def viscosityUnit := kilogram / (meter * second)</code></pre>

